               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp> „<cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> alveare </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> alvearium </quote></cit> ut videtur, ut: <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> mel, dum est </quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኀበ፡ መላጽያኒሁ፡ ውስተ፡ ገዳም፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> in alvearibus suis in sylva </quote></cit>, mss. Colb.“; sic ait Ludolfus in <lbl expand="lexicon">lex.</lbl> <lbl expand="columna">col.</lbl> 62. Equidem in <ref cRef="Gad. Lal." loc="">Gad. Lal. </ref> reperi formas <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምላጺ፡</foreign> et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምላጼ፡</foreign>, sed sensus loci, ubi reperitur, non perspicuus est. De etymo nihil statuere audeo, priusquam et forma et significatio nominis certis exemplis probatae sint. – Alveare alias <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀፎ፡</foreign> significat. </sense>
               
